title.narrative: Promotion of Bio-Ethanol as Alternative Fuel for Cooking in the United Republic of Tanzania

description.narrative: Tanzania's cooking energy requirements in urban and rural households are mainly met through charcoal and fuel wood respectively having serious impacts on people's health, as well as the environment. The GEF 6 project aims to replace this usage with bio-ethanol cook stoves by promoting the adoption of clean cooking practices using alternate fuels like bio-ethanol, establishing distilleries for producing fuel grade bio-ethanol, and supporting the local fabrication of bio-ethanol cook stoves..
